msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SINOPSIS:\n"
"    How to setup PHP4 with Apache2 and ht://Dig.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:13
msgid ""
"HINT: When I first try to compile PHP4 for Apache 2, I couldn't because of "
"the new layered I/O support implemented. I read the README in "
"sapi/apache2filter, but it didn't help and didn't want to go back to "
"apache-1.3.x, so this is how I had to do it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:16
msgid ""
"You can download apache from http://httpd.apache.org and PHP from "
"http://www.php.net. I'm going to use httpd-2.0.39.tar.gz and "
"php-4.2.1.tar.bz2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:19
msgid "httpd-2.0.39:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:23
msgid ""
"#Remember to change '--prefix=' to reflect the layout in your system, I "
"prefer #to use a non-standard location for these packages. If you built LFS, "
"you should #have installed openssl and perl, if not remove these options "
"from configure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:30
msgid ""
"tar -zxvf httpd-2.0.39.tar.gz cd httpd-2.0.39 ./configure "
"--prefix=/opt/httpd-2.0.39 --enable-ssl --enable-cgi --enable-so \\ "
"--enable-modules=all --with-perl --enable-shared=max make make install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:33
msgid ""
"Check if you have a nobody user defined, if not add it with useradd, "
"something like: 'useradd nobody' should suffice. Now let see if everything "
"went fine:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:35 origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:83
msgid "/opt/httpd-2.0.39/bin/apachectl start"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:41
msgid ""
"Use lynx, nmap, netstat or whatever tool you use to see if the server is "
"running. If you have lynx: 'lynx http://localhost/' will give you a page "
"that shows a successfully installation of apache. If you don't have it you "
"could use 'netstat -l | grep www', will show a line similar to this one: "
"'tcp\t0\t0 *:www\t\t*.*\tLISTEN'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:43
msgid "Now, that we are sure:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:45
msgid "/opt/httpd-2.0.39/bin/apachectl stop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:47
msgid ",just for a while to install PHP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:50
msgid "php-4.2.1:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:53
msgid "tar -jxvf php-4.2.1.tar.bz2 cd php-4.2.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:57
msgid ""
"#PHP gives you tons of options, use the ones that you need. Check them with "
"#'./configure --help'. If you don't have mysql installed, php will build a "
"#built-in module for it. I use the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:64
msgid ""
"./configure --prefix=/opt/httpd-2.0.39 \\ "
"--with-config-file-path=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf --without-pear --with-openssl "
"\\ --with-zlib --with-bz2 --enable-calendar --with-gdbm --with-db3 "
"--with-gmp \\ --with-mysql --with-ncurses --with-pgsql make make install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:66
msgid "OK, we have to add some options to /opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf/httpd.conf:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:73
msgid ""
"echo \"ScriptAlias /php/ \\\"/opt/httpd-2.0.39/bin/\\\"\" >> \\ "
"/opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf/httpd.conf echo \"Action application/x-httpd-php "
"\\\"/php/php\\\"\" >> \\ /opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf/httpd.conf echo \"AddType "
"application/x-httpd-php .php\" >> /opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf/httpd.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:77
msgid ""
"This is vital. Make sure you change /php/ to point to where you installed "
"these packages.  Create a test file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:79
msgid "echo \"<? phpinfo(); ?>\" > /opt/httpd-2.0.39/htdocs/test.php"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:81
msgid "It's time to see if everything went fine, restart the server with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:85
msgid "You'l need lynx or another web browser now, with lynx do:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:87
msgid "lynx http://localhost/test.php"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:90
msgid ""
"This page will show you information about PHP and your system. If you were "
"able to see it, the instalation was successful. You can delete test.php now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:92
msgid "Following the LFS style we...:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:94
msgid "ln -s /opt/httpd-2.0.39 /opt/apache2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:96
msgid "OK, now we need a boot script, create it with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:99
msgid "cat > /etc/rc.d/init.d/apache << \"EOF\" #!/bin/sh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:101
msgid "source /etc/rc.d/init.d/functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"case \"$1\" in\n"
"    start)\n"
"\techo \"Starting web server...\"\n"
"\tloadproc /opt/apache2/bin/httpd\n"
"\t;;\n"
"    stop)\n"
"\techo \"Stopping web server...\"\n"
"\tkillproc /opt/apache2/bin/httpd\n"
"\t;;\n"
"    restart)\n"
"\t$0 stop\n"
"\tsleep 1\n"
"\t$0 start\n"
"\t;;\n"
"    status)\n"
"\tstatusproc /opt/apache2/bin/httpd\n"
"\t;;\n"
"    *)\n"
"\techo \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart|status}\"\n"
"\texit 1\n"
"\t;;\n"
"esac\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:127
msgid "EOF chmod a+x /etc/rc.d/init.d/apache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:129
msgid "Remember to make the symlinks in /etc/rc.d/rc*.d."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:132
msgid "htdig-3.1.6:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:135
msgid ""
"An interesting package to be used in a web server is htdig, but it was very "
"tricky to install in my LFS. You can download it from http://www.htdig.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:138
msgid "tar -zxvf htdig-3.1.6.tar.gz cd htdig-3.1.6"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:141
msgid ""
"cp configure configure.bak sed -e \"s/ofstream=1/ofstream=0/\" configure.bak "
"> configure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:152
msgid ""
"I had to do this because it didn't recognize my gcc instalation.  Edit "
"htlib/htString.h to force it to use iostream.h, comment it like this: ...  "
"// #ifdef HAVE_OSTREAM_H // #include <ostream.h> // #endif // #ifdef "
"HAVE_IOSTREAM_H #include <iostream.h> // #endif ..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:155
msgid ""
"Only leave '#include <iostream.h>' uncommented. Now we won't have any "
"trouble doing:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:165
msgid ""
"./configure --prefix=/opt/httpd-2.0.39 \\ "
"--with-config-dir=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/conf \\ "
"--with-common=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/common \\ "
"--with-database-dir=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/db \\ "
"--with-cgi-bin-dir=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/cgi-bin \\ "
"--with-image-dir=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/htdocs/htdig \\ "
"--with-search-dir=/opt/httpd-2.0.39/htdocs/htdig make make install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:171
msgid ""
"To start using it, you have to edit /opt/apache2/conf/htdig.conf. As an "
"example change 'start_url:' to 'http://localhost/' and run: "
"'/opt/apache2/bin/rundig'.  It will take a while to build the search "
"database, you can safely ignore any warning message. To give it a try: 'lynx "
"http://localhost/htdig/search.html'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/apache2+php4+htdig.txt:174
msgid ""
"Voila! We're done. Remember to change all configuration files to reflect "
"your system layout and run 'rundig' again, also to read all "
"documentation. Good luck."
msgstr ""

